parameters.text:
=You are an expert technical writer and data processor. Your task is to analyze Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) content and generate structured training materials strictly in valid JSON format.

MAIN CONTENT:
{{$json["File_text_input"]}}

ADDITIONAL CONTEXT:
{{$json["text_input"]}}

TASK:
Generate structured training content in JSON format. Use MAIN CONTENT as the primary source. Use ADDITIONAL CONTEXT only if relevant. Ensure full coverage of important information.

OUTPUT FORMAT (STRICT JSON):
{
  "summary": {
    "title": "string",
    "key_points": ["point1", "point2", "point3"]
  },
  "training": {
    "title": "string",
    "steps": [
      {
        "step_number": 1,
        "title": "string",
        "description": "detailed explanation"
      }
    ]
  },
  "quiz": {
    "title": "string",
    "questions": [
      {
        "question": "string",
        "options": ["Option A", "Option B", "Option C", "Option D"],
        "correct_answer": "string",
        "explanation": "why this is correct"
      }
    ]
  }
}

CONTENT RULES:
1. Summary: 6–10 key points covering all major concepts.
2. Training Steps: 5–8 clear and actionable steps.
3. Quiz: 3–5 questions. Each must have exactly 4 options. Include the correct answer exactly as it appears in the options, plus an explanation.
4. Ensure clean, readable, high-quality content. Do not include null or empty fields.

STRICT JSON SYNTAX RULES (CRITICAL):
1. DO NOT output anything outside the JSON object. No conversational text, no introductions, no explanations.
2. DO NOT wrap the output in Markdown blocks (e.g., do not use ```json or ```). Output raw text only.
3. You MUST properly escape all double quotes within strings using a backslash (e.g., \"quoted text\"). Never leave stray or unescaped quotes.
4. Avoid using newlines (\n) inside string values unless absolutely necessary, and ensure they are properly escaped.
5. No trailing commas at the end of arrays or objects.
6. The final output must be perfectly parsable by standard JSON.parse() functions.

parameters.jsCode:
const data = $input.first().json;

// 1. Gather Summary content
const summaryTitle = data.summary.title || "";
const summaryPoints = data.summary.key_points ? data.summary.key_points.join(". ") : "";
const summaryText = `${summaryTitle}. ${summaryPoints}`;

// 2. Gather Training content
let trainingText = "";
if (data.training && data.training.steps) {
  trainingText = data.training.steps.map(step => {
    return `Step ${step.step_number}: ${step.title} - ${step.description}`;
  }).join(". ");
}

// 3. Combine Summary and Training into one string
// We use .replace(/\s+/g, ' ') to clean up any extra spaces
const combinedContent = `${summaryText}. ${trainingText}`.replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();

// 4. Return the simple JSON
return [
  {
    json: {
      content: combinedContent
    }
  }
];

// Get both inputs from Merge node
const items = $input.all();

// Identify which item is which
let content = null;
let presentation = null;

for (const item of items) {
  if (item.json.summary) {
    content = item.json;
  } else if (item.json.status === "completed") {
    presentation = item.json;
  }
}

// Safety checks
if (!content) {
  throw new Error("Content (summary/training/quiz) not found");
}

if (!presentation || presentation.status !== "completed") {
  throw new Error("Presentation not ready yet");
}

// Final merged output
const finalOutput = {
  summary: content.summary,
  training: content.training,
  quiz: content.quiz,
  presentation: {
    status: presentation.status,
    message: presentation.message,
    presentation_id: presentation.data.presentation_id,
    download_url: presentation.data.path,
    edit_url: presentation.data.edit_path,
    credits_used: presentation.data.credits_consumed
  }
};

return [
  {
    json: finalOutput
  }
];

let data = $input.first().json;

let parsed;

// Case 1: If AI returned JSON as string inside "output"
if (typeof data.output === "string") {
  try {
    parsed = JSON.parse(data.output);
  } catch (e) {
    throw new Error("Invalid JSON string in 'output'");
  }
} 
// Case 2: If AI already returned proper JSON
else if (typeof data === "object") {
  parsed = data;
} 
// Fallback
else {
  throw new Error("Unexpected AI response format");
}

// If it's wrapped in array → unwrap
if (Array.isArray(parsed)) {
  parsed = parsed[0];
}

return [
  {
    json: parsed
  }
];
